'''Marvin Keller''' (born 3 July 2002) is a Swiss professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for Swiss club [[BSC Young Boys|Young Boys]] and the [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland national team]].

==Club career==
Keller began playing [[goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] after his father bought him goalie gloves as a joke. He is a youth product of [[Grasshopper Club Zürich|Grasshoppers]], having joined their youth academy at the age of 7.<ref name="auto">{{Cite web|url=https://sportal.ch/bsc-young-boys/1128625/ploetzlich-im-yb-rampenlicht-nachdem-seine-goalie-karriere-aus-einem-jux-heraus-startete|title=Live Sport und News|website=sport.ch}}</ref> He was promoted to their U21s in the 2019–20 season, and was called up to their bench as backup goalkeeper in the [[Swiss Challenge League]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bernerzeitung.ch/wie-ein-30-jaehriger-in-einem-zehn-jahre-juengeren-koerper-352875660634|title=YB-Goalie Marvin Keller – Wie ein 30-Jähriger in einem zehn Jahre jüngeren Körper|date=25 May 2023|website=[[Berner Zeitung]]}}</ref> On 8 January 2020, he signed a professional contract with Grasshoppers until 2020 and was formally promoted to their senior team as third goalkeeper.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fussball.ch/GC+befoerdert+Marvin+Keller+und+Elias+Mesonero/699964/detail.htm?ref=rss,%20https://m.fussball.ch/GC+befoerdert+Marvin+Keller+und+Elias+Mesonero/699964/detail.htm?ref=rss|title=GC befördert Marvin Keller und Elias Mesonero. Von psc|first=VADIAN NET|last=AG|website=www.fussball.ch}}</ref> After 12 years with Grasshoppers, he transferred to [[FC Wil]] on 8 June 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gcz.ch/en/news/article/17/marvin-keller-switches-to-wil-20210608/|title=MARVIN KELLER SWITCHES TO WIL|website=www.gcz.ch}}</ref> On 24 March 2022, he extended his contract with the club until 2024 after cementing the starting spot in the squad.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://fcwil.ch/2022/05/24/torhueter-keller-verlaengert-beim-fc-wil-1900/|title=Torhüter Keller verlängert beim FC Wil 1900|date=24 May 2022|website=FC Wil, ein Sportverein, Fussball Club und Nachwuchsförderer}}</ref> He transferred to the [[Swiss Super League]] club [[BSC Young Boys|Young Boys]] on 12 February 2023 after they activated his release clause after a season-ending injury to their starting goalkeeper [[David von Ballmoos]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dieostschweiz.ch/artikel/marvin-keller-wechselt-zum-bsc-young-boys-vRXRRPQ|title=Marvin Keller wechselt zum BSC Young Boys|website=www.dieostschweiz.ch}}</ref> He made his professional debut with Young Boys in a 1–1 Swiss Super League tie with [[FC Zürich]] on 14 May 2023.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nau.ch/sport/fussball/yb-11-remis-zuhause-im-wankdorf-gegen-den-fc-zurich-66494807|title=YB: 1:1-Remis zuhause im Wankdorf gegen den FC Zürich|first=Matthias|last=Neuhaus|website=Nau}}</ref> He started 3 matches of the season as Grasshoppers won the [[2023–24 Swiss Super League]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.baerntoday.ch/sport/fussball/die-young-boys-gewinnen-das-letzte-meisterschaftsspiel-gegen-winterthur-21-151751698|title=Die Young Boys gewinnen das letzte Meisterschaftsspiel gegen Winterthur 2:1|date=29 May 2023|website=BärnToday}}</ref> He also started for Young Boys in the [[2022–23 Swiss Cup]] final against [[FC Lugano]] on 4 June 2023 after the second goalkeeper [[Anthony Racioppi]] was out injured, and made crucial saves as his team won 3–2 to win the cup.<ref name="Raz 2023">{{cite web | last=Raz | first=Florian | title=Nach dem Cupfinal – YB gegen Lugano – prägt dieses Duell bald den Schweizer Fussball? | website=Zürichsee-Zeitung | date=4 June 2023 | url=https://www.tagesanzeiger.ch/yb-gegen-lugano-praegt-dieses-duell-bald-den-schweizer-fussball-562415735066 | language=de | access-date=4 June 2023}}</ref>

On 13 September 2023, Keller joined [[FC Winterthur|Winterthur]] on loan.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Winterthur|url=https://fcwinterthur.ch/news/2023-09/marvin-keller-verstaerkt-das-goalieteam|title=MARVIN KELLER VERSTÄRKT DAS GOALIETEAM|trans-title=MARVIN KELLER STRENGTHENS THE GOALIE TEAM|date=13 September 2023|access-date=13 September 2023|language=de}}</ref>

==International career==
Born in [[London]], England, Keller is of Swiss descent.<ref name="auto"/> He is a youth international for Switzerland, having played up to the [[Switzerland national under-21 football team|Switzerland U21]]s.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rts.ch/sport/football/14061557-equipe-de-suisse-m21-la-suisse-avec-deux-mondialistes.html|title=Equipe de Suisse M21: la Suisse avec deux "mondialistes"|date=30 May 2023|website=RTSSport.ch}}</ref>

Keller was called up to the senior [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland]] squad for the [[Exhibition game#Association football|friendly]] matches against [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]] and the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]] on 7 and 10 June 2025, respectively.<ref>{{cite news |date=22 May 2025 |title=Männer-Nationalteam: Arrivierte Kräfte und ein Neuling für die Länderspiele in Nordamerika |trans-title=Men's national team: established players and a newcomer for the international matches in North America |url= https://www.football.ch/sfv/nationalteams/a-team/news/maenner-nationalteam-arrivierte-kraefte-und-ein-neuling-fuer-die-laenderspiele-in-nordamerika.aspx |language=de |publisher=[[Swiss Football Association]] |access-date=18 June 2025}}</ref>

